{"id": "food_FOOD00798", "name": "Evaporated milk (food medium)", "category": "food", "organism_scope": "food microbiome / general", "aerobic": true, "description": "Food-derived medium: metabolizable components of Evaporated milk [Milk and milk products] from FooDB, plus a standard M9 mineral base. Organic components use presence-based uptake bounds; FooDB content retained. Measured compounds with no BiGG exchange are listed under uncovered.", "namespace": "bigg", "provenance": {"source_type": "database", "citation": "FooDB v2020-04-07 (Wishart DS et al., foodb.ca). Content sources: USDA.", "doi": "", "url": "https://foodb.ca/downloads", "notes": "Organic components mapped from FooDB compounds to BiGG via InChIKey/name. Mineral base added. Bounds presence-based; foodb_content retained. Unmapped measured compounds kept in uncovered (v2 completeness fix). IMPORTANT: composition values are taken from the archived FooDB 2020-04-07 CSV data release; FooDB's live food page no longer displays this bulk composition, so it will appear empty. Verify individual compounds via the per-component cross-reference links. Underlying content was aggregated by FooDB from USDA / DTU / Phenol Explorer.", "data_release": "FooDB 2020-04-07 CSV release (foodb.ca/downloads)", "food_record": "https://foodb.ca/foods/FOOD00798", "verification": "expert-curated (multi-source food composition; growth-relevant profile completed, FooDB noise removed)", "curation_date": "2026-07-17", "curation_sources": [], "curation_notes": "Dominant carbon/energy sources for a microbe growing on this medium are LACTOSE (~10 g/100g, ~292 mM) and CITRIC ACID (~0.3 g/100g, ~16 mM); casein/whey amino acids (glutamate/leucine/proline-rich) are the main N source. Proximates, minerals and vitamins are USDA FoodData Central 'Milk, evaporated, whole' (11211050); amino acids from USDA evaporated-milk records with the remainder scaled from the bovine-milk AA profile to 6.8 g protein; organic acids scaled from fluid-milk citrate/orotate/lactat", "curation_added": ["lactose (the dominant fermentable sugar - was entirely absent; only erroneous sucrose was listed)", "citric acid (dominant organic acid ~0.3 g/100g - organic acids were entirely missing)", "orotic acid", "L-lactic acid", "L-valine", "L-phenylalanine", "trace free D-glucose and D-galactose", "iodide (genuine milk trace mineral)", "major fatty acids: palmitic C16:0, oleic C18:1, myristic C14:0, stearic C18:0, butyric C4:0, linoleic C18:2 (only C6/C8/C10/C12 were present)"], "curation_removed": [{"name": "Sucrose C12H22O11", "reason": "Evaporated milk is UNSWEETENED - it contains no sucrose; its sugar is lactose. FooDB/record mis-assignment. (Sucrose would only belong to SWEETENED condensed milk.) Replaced with lactose."}, {"name": "D-Serine", "reason": "Milk serine is the L-enantiomer; D-Serine is a mapping error. Replaced with L-serine."}, {"name": "Nickel", "reason": "Nickel in milk is a trace contaminant (single-digit ug/L), not a growth nutrient; drop as non-nutritive trace element."}, {"name": "CO2 CO2", "reason": "Dissolved gas / matrix species, not a growth nutrient supplied by the food."}, {"name": "O2 O2", "reason": "Dissolved gas / environmental species, not a food-supplied nutrient."}, {"name": "H+", "reason": "Proton / pH bookkeeping species, not a nutrient."}, {"name": "Ammonium", "reason": "Not a defined nutrient of intact evaporated milk (trace NPN only); non-informative as a supplied component."}], "curation_confidence": "high"}, "components": [{"name": "water", "bigg_metabolite": "h2o", "exchange": "EX_h2o_e", "lower_bound": -1000.0, "upper_bound": 1000.0, "concentration_mM": null, "xref": {"reactome": "R-ALL-109276", "kegg": "C00001", "chebi": "CHEBI:10743", "kegg_drug": "D00001", "hmdb": "HMDB01039", "biocyc": "META:CPD-15815", "mnx": "WATER", "inchikey": "XLYOFNOQVPJJNP-UHFFFAOYSA-N", "seed": "cpd00001", "metacyc": "WATER", "sabiork": "40", "inchi": "InChI=1S/H2O/h1H2", "formula": "H2O"}, "in_biggr": true, 